               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 4r-134v)
 -
                     Säqoqawä näfs “Lament of the Soul” (fols. 12vb l.20-16vb l.11)
 - Discourse
                     of St Athanasius on death (fols. 116rb l.2–120vb, l.22)
 - Homily of ʾAbbā
                     Salāmā, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols. 125rb l.6–127ra l.10)
 - Ṣalota
                     burāke za-ʾanǝst “The Prayer of the Blessing for Women” (fol. 134ra l.1–vb
                     l.8)
 
 Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The Ms. seems to have been copied from a printed book.</note>
                     <note>Starting from <locus target="#106vb">106vb</locus> l.7, the handwriting
                        becomes finer and more compressed, the hand apparently remaining the
                        same.</note>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1"> [<locus target="#132vb">132vb</locus>] ተፈጸመ፡ ዝንቱ፡
                        መጽሐፍ፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፫ለታሕሣሥ፡ በ፲ወ፱፻፸ወ፭፡ ዓ፡ ም፡ ወአጽሐፈቶ፡ ዓመተ፡ ማርያም፡ ገ፡ መስ፡ ኡራ፡ በንዋያ፡ {፫፻ወ፳፡
                        ብሩር፡} ወወሀበቶ፡ ለታቦተ፡ ቂርቆስ፡ ኡራ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርሐ፡ ኀበ፡ ሕይወት፡ ዘለዓለም፡ ምስለ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ አበዊነ፡
                        ወአኃዊነ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ገብረ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወለተ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ዓመተ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡
                        ወጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ለዓለ፡ ዓለ፡ አ፡ ወአ፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን፨ [<locus target="#132vb">132vb</locus>] This book was completed on the 13th of
                        Tāḫśāś, 1975 A.M. ʿĀmata Māryām Gä[brä] Mäs[qäl] (from) ʾUra had it written
                        with her money, 320 Bǝrr, and donated it to the tabot of Qirqos ʾUra so that it
                        might be for her the guide towards eternal life, together with all our fathers
                        and brothers: Gabra Masqal, Gabra Giyorgis, Walatta Ḥǝywat, Walatta Ṣādǝqān
                        [and] ʾAmata Māryām. He who stole it or erased its (text) shall be
                        excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul for ever and ever. Amen and
                        amen. So be it, so be it. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
               </msContents>
